# Pixhawk Firmware – Solar Powered AI Glider

## Overview

The aircraft uses the ArduPlane firmware from ArduPilot running on a Pixhawk flight controller.

This firmware enables stable, autonomous, and efficient flight for a solar-powered fixed-wing glider by integrating sensor data and controlling flight surfaces in real time.

---

## Core Capabilities

The firmware provides:

* Autopilot stabilization
* Sensor fusion (IMU, GPS, barometer, compass)
* Multiple flight modes
* Telemetry communication
* Mission planning and waypoint navigation
* Failsafe and return-to-launch (RTL) safety features

It converts pilot inputs and mission commands into real-time control signals for the aircraft.

---

## Control Outputs

The Pixhawk generates PWM signals to control:

| Output  | Component            |
| ------- | -------------------- |
| SERVO 1 | Aileron              |
| SERVO 2 | Elevator             |
| SERVO 3 | Rudder               |
| SERVO 4 | ESC (Motor throttle) |

---

## Sensor Inputs

The flight controller reads data from:

* IMU → Orientation and stabilization
* GPS → Position and velocity
* Barometer → Altitude estimation
* Compass → Heading direction

---

## Flight Modes Used

| Mode      | Purpose                         |
| --------- | ------------------------------- |
| Manual    | Full pilot control              |
| Stabilize | Assisted manual flight          |
| FBWA      | Angle-limited stabilized flight |
| Auto      | Fully autonomous mission        |
| RTL       | Return-to-launch safety mode    |

---

## Why ArduPlane?

ArduPlane is ideal for this project because it supports:

* Fixed-wing aircraft
* Autonomous flight missions
* Gliding and motor-assisted flight
* Real-time telemetry and logging
* Robust failsafe systems

This makes it well-suited for research and prototype UAV development.

---

## Ground Control Software

Mission planning and configuration are performed using Mission Planner.

This software is used to:

* Upload firmware
* Calibrate sensors
* Configure flight modes
* Upload autonomous missions
* Monitor telemetry and logs

---

## Firmware Installation Steps

1. Connect Pixhawk to a computer via USB
2. Open Mission Planner
3. Navigate to "Install Firmware"
4. Select "ArduPlane"
5. Wait for firmware flashing to complete

---

## Safety & Failsafe Features

The system includes:

* Low battery Return-to-Launch (RTL)
* Loss of signal failsafe
* GPS failsafe
* Geofence protection

These features ensure safe and reliable autonomous operation.

---

## Solar Integration

The glider integrates a solar charging system using an MPPT controller (CN3722).

* Solar panels provide supplementary power during flight
* Battery voltage is monitored by the flight controller
* Future integration will include solar-aware flight optimization

